{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637630","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637630"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:46:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:46:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17675"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17675","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17675"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.25,0.54,0.04,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10389"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72124"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10389"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17675"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57594"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"10505"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24277"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24367"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72124","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72124"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe early distal tubule plays an important role in urinary concentration and dilution.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes solute transport in the early distal tubule?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Calcium and magnesium reabsorption only","Active sodium reabsorption with passive water follow","Sodium and chloride reabsorption via sodium chloride cotransporter","Sodium and bicarbonate reabsorption","Sodium reabsorption in exchange for potassium secretion"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esodium and chloride reabsorption via sodium chloride cotransporter\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary transport mechanism in the early distal tubule. This electroneutral cotransporter moves sodium and chloride in a 1:1 ratio and is specifically inhibited by thiazide diuretics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eactive sodium reabsorption with passive water follow\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because the early distal tubule is water-impermeable, preventing passive water movement.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esodium reabsorption in exchange for potassium secretion\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as this process occurs in the late distal tubule and collecting duct via the sodium-potassium ATPase.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esodium and bicarbonate reabsorption\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because bicarbonate reabsorption occurs predominantly in the proximal tubule.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecalcium and magnesium reabsorption only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because while some calcium reabsorption occurs, the primary function is sodium chloride reabsorption.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe impermeability to water makes this segment important for diluting the urine. The sodium chloride cotransporter\u0027s activity can be regulated to help maintain sodium balance and blood pressure.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The early distal tubule reabsorbs sodium and chloride via the sodium chloride cotransporter.","The sodium chloride cotransporter is the target of thiazide diuretics.","The early distal tubule is impermeable to water, making it a diluting segment."],"references":["Hall JE, Hall ME. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020.","Tortora, G. J., Mellifont, R., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Peoples, G., D, D. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, Asia-Pacific Edition,  2nd Edition. John Wiley \u0026 Sons Australia; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57594"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17675"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57594"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T22:52:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T22:52:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10389"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72124"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4933","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4933"},"attribut